Scratchpad for Spring webapp code samples
-----------------------------------------

Demonstrates the capabilities of the Spring MVC web framework through small, simple examples. Framework version illustrated: Spring MVC 3.1.

Starting as an incremental copy of the SpringSource Spring MVC Showcase project at https://github.com/SpringSource/spring-mvc-showcase, adding a single 'tab' at a time.

- The simplest possible @Controller
- Mapping Requests
- Obtaining Request Data
- Generating Responses
- Message Converters
- Rendering Views
- Type Conversion
- Validation
- Forms
- File Upload
- Exception Handling

Source code
-----------
Clone the repository:
$ git clone git://github.com/gerjantd/springpad.git

See http://help.github.com if you need help with git.

Run
---	
From the command line with Maven:
$ cd springpad
$ mvn tomcat:run

or

In your preferred IDE such as SpringSource Tool Suite (STS) or IDEA:
- Import springpad as a Maven Project
- Drag-n-drop the project onto the "SpringSource tc Server Developer Edition" or another Servlet 2.5 or > Server to run, such as Tomcat.

Access the deployed web application at: http://localhost:8080/springpad/
